Marital Violations

As you study the reign of David, you'll notice his anguish as he had to constantly fight with issues surrounding his children. Amnon raped his own sister, Absolam killed his brother Amnon, Absolam was banished and subsequently led a revolt against his father, Adonijah claimed the kingship over Solomon without David's blessing, and a host of other issues.

Where did this all start? It started with a violation of marital covenant. David, knowing Bathsheba was married, summoned her and violated an innocent man's marriage. This leads to cover up, scandal, murder, and the death of a newborn. The Prophet Nathan's declarations of the issues David would face were stemmed from the Lord's anger towards the actions of the King.

Today, marriage is STILL sacred yet we find it more easy to violate the covenant than at any other time. As you turn on the news to see so much violence and so many issues facing families I wonder . . . do the same conclusions towards David's violations stand? 
Join me in praying for marriages today. Violations of the covenant have serious repercussions that may not be immediately seen. Note that David's major battles from the violation didn't show up until the next generation. Lord, strengthen, restore, and give us wisdom for our marriages. Our family lines depend on it.
